formThreeIdData.notesToCertificate:
1.We have relied upon & verified the estimates given by the management in case of costs other than construction cost.					
2.The preparation of the accompanying Statement is the responsibility of the Management of the Company. This responsibility includes designing, implementing and maintaining internal control relevant to the preparation and presentation of the Statement,and applying an appropriate basis of preparation; and making estimates that are reasonable in the circumstances.					
3.The certificate is addressed to and provided to the promoters of the project solely for the purpose to enable comply with requirement of RERA , and should not be used by any other person or for any other purpose.					
4.The details mentioned in Annexure A such as carpet area, booking status, unit consideration, date of agreement to sale, encumbrance status, name, KYC and mobile numbers of allottees are as provided by the management. Received amount has been verified with the books of accounts.					
5. The Promoter of the project has agreed to pay consideration to the land owners in form of constructed area and 8% of the total gross revenue. The 8% share in total gross revenue comes to Rs. 1,51,27,672/- and constructed area worth of Rs. 2,31,72,328/- (as per clause 8(a)(i) & 42 of the development agreement). Therefore, the total land cost comes to Rs. 3,83,00,000/-					
6. The expenses in relation to Stampy duty & registration fees, FSI cost and payments to statutory authority have been made by the land owners  and therefore it is consider as inccured and paid					
7. There are in total 3 projects which are being developed in FP. (5+6+7+8+28+89)/2 for which the total FSI cost as per its receipt and payment schedules comes to Rs. 2,33,20,500/-. This FSI cost is allocated to the respective project on the basis of its FSI utilisation. FSI utilisation as per plan passed is 6195.39 sq mtr out of total FSI utilisation of 34098.12 sq mtr. Therefore, FSI cost of Royal Radiance comes to Rs. 42,37,172/-					
8. There are in total 3 projects which are being developed in FP. (5+6+7+8+28+89)/2 for which the total FSI  paid comes to Rs. 58,30,125/- This FSI cost is allocated to the respective project on the basis of its FSI utilisation. FSI utilisation as per plan passed is 6195.39 sq mtr out of total FSI utilisation of 34098.12 sq mtr.Therefore the FSI paid for this project is Rs. 10,59,293/-					
9. The same base is taken for statutory payments made to authorities as per note no. 7. Total expenditure (for 3 projects) excluding FSI cost is Rs. 1,09,07,211. Therefore, statutory payments to authorities for the project Royal Radiance comes to Rs. 19,81,764/-					
					
10. The unit number 1 to 6 (Shops) have been alloted to the land owners as per the condition mentioend in Development Agreement. There are two land owners and therefore name of both land owners are mentioned in form 3A.
